==English==

===Etymology===
This unique type of goal was named after Argentine striker Cesareo Onzari’s (at left) corner kick that spun directly into the goal for Argentina against the reigning Olympic champion Uruguay in a 1924 friendly.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|football}} A goal scored directly from a [[corner kick]] without any other player - on either team - touching or otherwise deflecting the ball into the goal.

